          "type": "text",
          "name": "help_text",
          "value": "In this routine a teacher leads their students to count aloud together and find patterns. Decide on a skip count amount, whether to count up or down, a number to start on, and the range of numbers to use. Record each number on a board in an organized manner (designed in advance) as each number is spoken. Students notice patterns and discuss why those patterns occur.",
