                  "rows": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "name": "topics_text",
                      "value": "This activity can involve much deeper math practice than just rote counting. Writing the numbers on the board allows the students to look for patterns. It allows them to practice predicting and reasoning about which number should come next. Ask them \"What comes next?\" and \"Why do you think that is true?\"\n\nSkip counting is valuable for developing many skills.\n* Counting On – Count forward by 1s starting anywhere. This helps with beginning addition.\n* Counting Down by 1s – Helps with understanding the number order more deeply, and it also helps with beginning subtraction.\n* Skip Counting up or down – Helps with mental addition and subtraction. It also helps with multiplication and division.\n\n**Many Types of Numbers** While you will certainly start by counting and skip counting by whole numbers, choral counting is also a very effective routine for practicing with fractions, mixed numbers, or decimal numbers. Doing the skip counting and looking for patterns will give good practice and deeper understandings in all these areas.",
                      "_translations": {
                        "value": {}
                      },
                      "parameter_list": {
                        "icon_src": "help",
                        "style": "navigation"
                      },
                      "_nested_name": "dg_advice.accordion_for_intro.accord_topics.dg_topics_accord.topics_text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "_nested_name": "dg_advice.accordion_for_intro.accord_topics.dg_topics_accord"
